OL,3,CFamily of father who spent final days
OL,4,Cin hospice say 'it needs to stay open'
OL,6,FThe family of a father-of-three say
OL,7,Fthey "don't know what they would have
OL,8,Fdone" if it wasn't for a local hospice
OL,9,Fwho cared for him in the last few
OL,10,Fweeks of his life.
OL,12,FSteve Hughes, 46, was referred to
OL,13,FBlackpool's Trinity Hospice in 2024
OL,14,Fafter his stomach cancer spread to his
OL,15,Fbrain. Thanks to constant treatment
OL,16,Ffrom their staff he was able to say
OL,17,Fgoodbye to his loved ones before he
OL,18,Fdied.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
