OL,3,CFamily of father who spent final days
OL,4,Cin hospice say 'it needs to stay open'
OL,6,FPippa said: "It has to stay open.
OL,7,FSteve was 45 when he was diagnosed
OL,8,Fwith cancer - 46 when he died. If it
OL,9,Fcan happen to him it can happen to
OL,10,Fanyone.
OL,12,F"I can't imagine what it would be like
OL,13,Fwithout a hospice in your community.
OL,14,FYou'd either die at home alone or in a
OL,15,Fhospital not getting the care you
OL,16,Fdeserve."
OL,18,FIn 2024, will donations accounted for
OL,19,Falmost 20% of Trinity Hospice's income
OL,20,Fand is a vital source of funding which
OL,21,Fallows them to continue providing care.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
