OL,3,CFamily of father who spent final days
OL,4,Cin hospice say 'it needs to stay open'
OL,6,FHe said: "We're budgeting at the
OL,7,Fmoment for a potential operating loss
OL,8,Fnext year of over a #1 million."
OL,10,FIn 2010, Trinity Hospice received 40%
OL,11,Fof its funding from the Government,
OL,12,Fbut over the last 15 years it has
OL,13,Fdropped to 28%.
OL,15,FDavid said: "We provide end of life
OL,16,Fsupport for loved ones and bereavement
OL,17,Fcounselling, but the hospice cannot
OL,18,Fguarantee they'll continue to offer
OL,19,Fthose services."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
