OL,3,CFamily of father who spent final days
OL,4,Cin hospice say 'it needs to stay open'
OL,6,FThe hospice has already had to make
OL,7,Fcuts. Despite having an 18 bed
OL,8,Finpatient unit, they can only afford
OL,9,Fto take 14 patients.
OL,11,FDavid said: "Gifts in wills are
OL,12,Fcrucial to the survival and growth of
OL,13,Fhospices like ours, that's why we're
OL,14,Fasking our incredible supporters and
OL,15,Fcommunity to consider leaving a gift
OL,16,Fto our hospice."
OL,18,FAs well as providing crucial end of
OL,19,Flife care, David also argues hospices
OL,20,Fcan alleviate the pressures felt by
OL,21,Fthe NHS.
