OL,3,CFamily of father who spent final days
OL,4,Cin hospice say 'it needs to stay open'
OL,6,FPippa said: "Right from the start,
OL,7,FSteve knew he wanted to be at Trinity.
OL,8,FWe'd seen their compassion and care
OL,9,Fthe year before when my Dad was at the
OL,10,Fhospice, and knew it would be the
OL,11,Fright place for all of us to just have
OL,12,Ftime together, when the time came.
OL,14,F"As soon as he arrived at the hospice,
OL,15,Fthey assessed his symptoms and pain
OL,16,Fmanagement, and it was like I got
OL,17,FSteve back. For him to be awake and
OL,18,Fnot in pain was a miracle to us. It
OL,19,Fmeant the world to have a week just
OL,20,Fspeaking with him again."
